==Life support during clinical death==
The purpose of [[cardiopulmonary resuscitation]] (CPR) during [[cardiac arrest]] is ideally reversal of the clinically dead state by restoration of blood circulation and breathing. However there is great variation in the effectiveness of CPR for this purpose. Blood pressure is very low during manual CPR,<ref>{{cite journal
